==Continuity==
The opening crawl presented in the opening pages of the book refers to [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] as the "President" of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="RPG" /> This position would later instead become known as the [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellor]].<ref name="TPM">{{Film|I}}</ref>

The glossed-page section "No Job is Over This Little Guy's Head" giving [[in-universe]] details for the [[R2-series astromech droid/Legends|R2 unit]] implies that the R2 unit, and by extension [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]], was newly developed by the time of the Galactic Civil War.<ref name="RPG" /> However, in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']],<ref name="TPM" /> released [[1999|twelve years later]]<ref name="Year by Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, Updated and Expanded Edition]]''</ref> but set [[32 BBY/Legends|32 years]] before the [[original trilogy]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> R2-D2 not only was present, but also played a major role.<ref name="TPM" />

The events of "[[Rebel Breakout]]" were later adapted and serialized as a webstrip, ''[[Rookies: No Turning Back]]''. The strip was written and illustrated by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and published on [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club]], a section of [[StarWars.com|the official ''Star Wars'' website]], in [[2006]].

